  1040→VISUALIZATIONS OF INTERNAL ACTIVATIONS
  1041→We visualize the internal activations for a string template “x1 + x2 =” on the second numeric token
  1042→(x2). Values for x2 are selected as a range 0-999 (all values present by the vocab), and values for x1
  1043→are sampled randomly from the same range. Then, we project the activations of the model’s middle
  1044→layer to 64 dimensions with PCA and compute the Fourier transform.
  1045→We visualize the first 16 PCA dimensions in Figure 14 and the maximal magnitudes of the frequen-
  1046→cies in the Fourier transform in Figure 15. We visualize across model sizes and families.
